<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SFM & SFP: Agro-Product Fermentation & Food Security Simulator</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tailwindcss/browser@4"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
</head>
<body class="bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 font-sans p-6">

    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-6">
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-600 to-indigo-700 p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-xl">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
                <span class="bg-violet-900 text-violet-200 text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">SFP: Agro Product Tech</span>
                <span class="bg-indigo-900 text-indigo-200 text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">SFM: Food Security</span>
            </div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold mt-2">Agro-Product Fermentation Velocity & Quality Stability Simulator</h1>
            <p class="text-indigo-100 text-sm mt-1">Applying the First Derivative $f'(x)$ to Optimize Agro-Food Processing and Reduce Post-Harvest Food Loss in Malaysia</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 shadow-md">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-violet-400 mb-2">📌 Joint Bioscience Scenario: Bio-Processing Meets Supply Stability</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                In Malaysia's food sector, fermenting agro-products (such as commercial Tempeh or Cocoa beans) relies on controlled microbial growth. This biological population follows a **logistic S-shaped curve**. From an **Agro-Product Technology (SFP)** standpoint, we must track the exact chemical transition of the substrate. Simultaneously, from a **Food Security (SFM)** perspective, stopping the process too early causes spoilage, while delaying it leads to over-fermentation and severe food waste. 
                Using calculus, the **First Derivative $f'(x)$** identifies the <span class="font-semibold text-violet-300">Instantaneous Fermentation Velocity</span>. Halting production precisely at the Inflection Point guarantees peak nutritional quality and maximum shelf-life efficiency.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-slate-800/80 p-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 text-center">
                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400 font-semibold block mb-1">ORIGINAL FUNCTION: BIOMASS DENSITY</span>
                <div class="text-lg font-mono text-blue-400 bg-slate-900 p-3 rounded-lg inline-block my-2 w-full">
                    f(x) = K / (1 + &beta; &middot; e<sup>-k &middot; &eta; &middot; x</sup>)
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Measures total microbial culture concentration on hour x.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-slate-800/80 p-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 text-center">
                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400 font-semibold block mb-1">FIRST DERIVATIVE: INSTANTANEOUS FERMENTATION VELOCITY</span>
                <div class="text-lg font-mono text-violet-400 bg-slate-900 p-3 rounded-lg inline-block my-2 w-full">
                    f'(x) = (K &middot; &beta; &middot; k &middot; &eta; &middot; e<sup>-k&eta;x</sup>) / (1 + &beta;e<sup>-k&eta;x</sup>)<sup>2</sup>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Measures the bio-reaction speed dynamic changes (biomass/hour).</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 shadow-md">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-slate-200">📊 Kinetic Biomass Trajectory & Reaction Speed Chart</h2>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-4">Click anywhere on the chart lines or drag the timeline slider below to evaluate calculus parameters dynamically!</p>
            <div class="relative h-80 w-full mb-4 bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-xl">
                <canvas id="growthChart"></canvas>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-slate-900 p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 space-y-2">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-sm">
                    <span class="text-slate-400 font-medium">Interactive Timeline Controller:</span>
                    <span id="dayDisplay" class="text-xl font-bold text-violet-400 bg-slate-800 px-3 py-1 rounded">Hour 24</span>
                </div>
                <input type="range" id="daySlider" min="0" max="48" value="24" class="w-full h-2 bg-slate-700 rounded-lg appearance-none cursor-pointer accent-violet-500">
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="hudSection" class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl border border-violet-500/30 shadow-lg">
            <div class="p-3 bg-slate-900 rounded-lg">
                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400 block font-semibold">BIOMASS DENSITY f(x)</span>
                <span id="popValue" class="text-2xl font-black text-blue-400">0 mg/L</span>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 bg-slate-900 rounded-lg">
                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400 block font-semibold">REACTION VELOCITY f'(x)</span>
                <span id="rateValue" class="text-2xl font-black text-violet-400">0 mg/L/hr</span>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 bg-slate-900 rounded-lg">
                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400 block font-semibold">SUPPLY CHAIN STABILITY STATUS</span>
                <span id="statusValue" class="text-md font-bold block mt-1 text-yellow-400">Processing Phase</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-violet-950/40 border border-violet-800/60 p-5 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-violet-400 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">💡 Calculus Insights & Cross-Course Action (Layman's Terms)</h3>
            <p id="laymanText" class="text-slate-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">Adjust the timeline slider to view dynamic integrated SFP & SFM bio-feedback analysis.</p>
        </div>

    </div>

    <script>
        // Biological Constants for Agro-Food Fermentation (e.g., Rhizopus oligosporus)
        const K = 500;       // Maximum carrying capacity of biomass density
        const beta = 80;     // Scaling constant for inoculation
        const k = 0.18;      // Kinetic growth rate constant
        const eta = 1.0;     // Incubation Temperature Efficiency Index (1.0 = Optimum 32°C)

        // Mathematical Function f(x) - Logistic Curve
        function fx(x) {
            return K / (1 + beta * Math.exp(-k * eta * x));
        }

        // Mathematical Function f'(x) - First Derivative Equation
        function fPrimeX(x) {
            const expTerm = Math.exp(-k * eta * x);
            const numerator = K * beta * (k * eta) * expTerm;
            const denominator = Math.pow(1 + beta * expTerm, 2);
            return numerator / denominator;
        }

        // Generate Dataset Array for Hour 0 to 48
        const labels = [];
        const dataPopulation = [];
        const dataRate = [];
        for (let x = 0; x <= 48; x += 2) {
            labels.push(x);
            dataPopulation.push(fx(x).toFixed(1));
            dataRate.push(fPrimeX(x).toFixed(1));
        }

        // Chart.js Canvas Configuration
        const ctx = document.getElementById('growthChart').getContext('2d');
        const growthChart = new Chart(ctx, {
            type: 'line',
            data: {
                labels: labels,
                datasets: [
                    {
                        label: 'Biomass Density f(x) (mg/L)',
                        data: dataPopulation,
                        borderColor: '#3b82f6',
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1)',
                        yAxisID: 'y',
                        tension: 0.3
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Reaction Velocity f\'(x) (mg/L/hr)',
                        data: dataRate,
                        borderColor: '#8b5cf6',
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.1)',
                        yAxisID: 'y1',
                        tension: 0.3
                    }
                ]
            },
            options: {
                responsive: true,
                maintainAspectRatio: false,
                scales: {
                    y: {
                        type: 'linear',
                        display: true,
                        position: 'left',
                        grid: { color: '#334155' },
                        ticks: { color: '#94a3b8' }
                    },
                    y1: {
                        type: 'linear',
                        display: true,
                        position: 'right',
                        grid: { drawOnChartArea: false },
                        ticks: { color: '#94a3b8' }
                    },
                    x: {
                        grid: { color: '#334155' },
                        ticks: { color: '#94a3b8' },
                        title: { display: true, text: 'Fermentation Processing Duration (Hours)', color: '#94a3b8' }
                    }
                },
                plugins: {
                    legend: { labels: { color: '#f1f5f9' } }
                }
            }
        });

        // Dynamic State Engine to Update HUD Metrics & Descriptions
        function updateMetrics(hour) {
            document.getElementById('dayDisplay').innerText = `Hour ${hour}`;
            
            const pop = fx(hour);
            const rate = fPrimeX(hour);
            
            document.getElementById('popValue').innerText = `${Math.round(pop)} mg/L`;
            document.getElementById('rateValue').innerText = `${rate.toFixed(1)} mg/L/hr`;
            
            let status = "";
            let layman = "";
            
            // Strategic evaluations based on location relative to the Inflection Point (Around Hour 24)
            if (hour <= 16) {
                status = "🟡 UNDER-FERMENTED (SFP Risk)";
                layman = `At Hour ${hour}, the fermentation velocity $f'(x)$ is accelerating slowly at ${rate.toFixed(1)} mg/L/hr. From an <b>SFP (Agro Product)</b> perspective, the substrate properties are still unstable and raw. Harvesting now reduces product marketability and degrades structural quality metrics.`;
            } else if (hour > 16 && hour <= 30) {
                status = "🟢 OPTIMAL TEXTURE (SFP & SFM Peak)";
                layman = `Calculus proves that at Hour ${hour}, fermentation velocity is near its maximum speed (${rate.toFixed(1)} mg/L/hr) around the curve's <b>Inflection Point</b>. Stopping the bio-processing now guarantees premium agro-product quality (SFP) and maximizes structural shelf-life stability, reducing post-harvest supply waste (SFM).`;
            } else {
                status = "🔴 OVER-FERMENTED (SFM Food Loss)";
                layman = `By Hour ${hour}, although biomass density is maximum (${Math.round(pop)} mg/L), the derivative velocity $f'(x)$ has crashed down. The product is now over-fermented, releasing ammonia gas. This creates massive <b>SFM (Food Security)</b> concerns as the entire batch becomes inedible food waste, disrupting local supply lines.`;
            }
            
            document.getElementById('statusValue').innerText = status;
            document.getElementById('laymanText').innerHTML = layman;
        }

        // Input Slider Event Trigger
        const slider = document.getElementById('daySlider');
        slider.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
            updateMetrics(parseInt(e.target.value));
        });

        // Initialize display configuration on load
        updateMetrics(24);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
